4. Robustness of entanglement under bit Ô¨Çip channel
4.1. Evolution of special states under bit Ô¨Çip channel
The bit Ô¨Çip channel is the same as the dephasing channel under the local rotational transformation. It Ô¨Çips the state of a qubit between |0‚ü© and |1‚ü© with a certain probability and each qubit is affected by the noise correspondingly. The states |Œ¶n‚ü© in Eq. (13) and |Œ® n‚ü© in Eq. (5), which can be transformed into each other by local operations and manifest the most signiÔ¨Åcant difference in robustness under the dephasing channel, are worth to be investigated further for this channel. Similarly, we also take the example of the pure states |Œ¶4‚ü© and |Œ® 4‚ü© to calculate the negativities under the bit Ô¨Çip channel. We need to write the nonzero elements of the partial transposed density matrix œÅŒ¶TA4 (t) and œÅŒ®TA4 (t) during the evolution, which are given in Appendix A. Here the negativities expressions of |Œ¶n‚ü© with n = 2, 3, . . . , 7, are straightforwardly provided as follows:

